Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Halve @green bell peppers{2} lengthwise; remove stems and seeds. Toss on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}; arrange cut sides down. Trim @button mushrooms{4%oz}. Toss on empty side with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp}. Season with salt and pepper.

Roast on middle rack until peppers are lightly browned and softened and mushrooms are golden brown, ~{18-20%minutes}. Remove from oven.

> 4 SERVINGS: Divide between 2 baking sheets; roast bell peppers on middle rack and mushrooms on top rack.

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens. Finely dice @Roma tomato{1}(diced).

In a #small bowl{}, toss tomato with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}. Season with salt and pepper.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @almonds{1/2%oz}; cook, stirring often, until lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in scallion whites, @Israeli couscous{3/4%cup}, @Tunisian spice blend{2%tsp} (you'll use the rest later), and a pinch of salt. Cook, stirring, until scallion whites are softened and couscous is toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @water{3/4%cup} and @mushroom stock concentrate{1}. Bring to a boil; cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until tender, ~{6-8%minutes}. Keep covered off heat.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use a medium pot, 4 tsp Tunisian Spice, and 1 1/2 cups water.

> TIP: Drain any excess water from cooked couscous, if necessary.

Meanwhile, in a second small bowl, combine @Sabra® Classic Hummus{4%tbsp}, @sour cream{2%tbsp}, and remaining @Tunisian spice blend{1%tbsp}. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

Once mushrooms are cool enough to handle, transfer to a #cutting board{}; roughly chop.

Heat pot with couscous over medium-low heat. Uncover; stir in mushrooms, tomato, and @butter{1%tbsp}. Cook, stirring, until butter has melted and tomato is slightly softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt (we used 1/2 tsp) and pepper.

Stuff each bell pepper half with as much filling as will fit.

Divide remaining filling and stuffed peppers between plates. Drizzle with sauce. Top with @feta cheese{1/2%cup} and scallion greens and serve.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use 2 TBSP butter and 1 tsp salt.